<h2 id="editors-notes">Editor’s notes</h2>

<p>Guantanamera is a song I’ve had on my list for a few years now, and after a couple recent viewer requests it found itself on the top of the list. I first heard it via Pete Seeger, and in spending some time learning it discovered several other fun versions of it (The Sandpipers version is probably my favorite, musically). I’ll teach you the chords (no capo), some easy strumming patterns, and then crank up the difficulty a bit and show you a fancy intro riff as well as a few ways to add flourish while playing. I hope you enjoy!</p>

<p>Capo guide:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Capo 4 to play with Pete Seeger’s Carnegie Hall Concert version</li>
  <li>Capo 5 to play with the Sandpiper’s version</li>
  <li>Capo 6 to play with Pete Seeger’s Sweden 1968 version</li>
</ul>

<p>Video timestamps</p>

<ul>
  <li>0:00 Playthrough &amp; overview</li>
  <li>1:36 Chords needed</li>
  <li>3:45 Verse &amp; Chorus progressions</li>
  <li>6:10 Strumming patterns</li>
  <li>11:04 Fancy intro riff</li>
  <li>15:57 Adding melodic flourish</li>
  <li>17:39 Farewell</li>
</ul>

